For Screaming Vlog 36 we meet up with @salba69, @twistthewrist, @jake_wooten, and @catchsurf Pros @kalanirobb, @johnnyredmond, and @tylerstanaland at Catch Surf HQ in Encinitas, CA! After drying off from the water, we go from the waves to the 'crete as the squad heads to Poods Park to catch a session before calling it a day! Hit up our @youtube channel to watch now! For Screaming Vlog 32 we met up with SC Pro @jake_wooten at @whartonstwarehouse in Philly to officially welcome @_devinflynn to @redbullskate! Devin had no idea Jake was pulling up, so naturally he was already ripping at Wharton HQ. Once Jake hands Devin his new headwear, the session gets fired up to next level stoke! Jump in on the session with Devin, Jake, and the whole Wharton St. Crew and enjoy the celebratory session. Congrats again, Devin! Where should we go in the next Screaming Vlog? Let us know in the comments!
🎥: @trevarcushing
#SantaCruzSkateboards

node.text:
Today we are excited to skate @ktrchandler as we talk about and put to the test the 8.5 x 32.2 ’No Pattern' Everslick Deck! Everslick decks come equipped with a layer of material that slides longer, keeps graphics around and makes the board 5x more resistant to center focus breaks. This board also features amazing art by our friend Chuck Anderson aka @nopattern! Be sure to stop by your local shop and see if they have this one available. We put Santa Cruz Skateboards Brand Manager @andrewcannon to the test with three different challenges to find out how this setup skates! Hit up our @youtube channel to watch now, then let us know in the comments below which challenges we should throw in the bins next!
👉 This weeks product setup:
8.5 x 32.2 @nopattern Everslick Deck
149 Standard @independenttrucks
@rictawheels Chrome Cores 53mm 99A
@bronsonspeedco Ceramics
7/8ths Indy Allen Bolts
Graphic @mobgrip 🏁💨
🎥: @ericdanescu
#SantaCruzSkateboards

node.text:
Today we are excited to talk about and put to the test the 7.75 x 31.6 Transcend Dots VX Deck! This board comes equipped with 5 normal plys and 2 layers of our Quad X technology, making these boards super strong. Be sure to stop by your local shop and see if they have this one available. We are also stoked to try out the new @rictawheels Speedrings! Speedrings’ unique core design puts urethane around the bearing bore like a non-cored wheel, giving you the feeling of a traditional wheel with the speed and reduced rolling resistance of a cored wheel. We put Santa Cruz Skateboards Brand Manager @andrewcannon to the test with three different challenges to find out how this setup skates! Hit up our @youtube channel to watch now, and let us know in the comments below what challenges we should throw in the bins next!
👉 This weeks product setup:
7.75 x 31.6 'Transcend Dots' VX Deck
139 Standard @independenttrucks
@rictawheels Speedrings
